text: Cypress is an unincorporated community in Union Township, Vanderburgh County, in the U.S. state of Indiana. ==History== An old variant name of the community was called Dogtown. A post office was established under the name Cypress in 1882, and remained in operation until 1933. ==Geography== Cypress is located at . ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Vanderburgh County, Indiana Category:Unincorporated communities in Indiana
